"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"gratipay","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":1340076,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::ReportSeverityUpdated","message":"","markdown_message":"","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2016-12-04T18:34:34.566Z","updated_at":"2016-12-04T18:34:34.566Z","additional_data":{},"actor":{"username":"dmk246","cleared":false,"url":"/dmk246","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"/assets/avatars/default-71a302d706457f3d3a31eb30fa3e73e6cf0b1d677b8fa218eaeaffd67ae97918.png"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"gratipay","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false}],"activity_page_count":1,"activity_page_number":1,"summaries":[{"id":2083,"category":"team","content":"The suggestion was to set `X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: master-only`. From [Adobe](https://www.adobe.com/devnet-docs/acrobatetk/tools/AppSec/xdomain.html) ([per](https://github.com/twitter/secureheaders/issues/88)):\n\n\u003e Normally a meta-policy is declared in the master policy file, but for those who can’t write to the root directory, they can also declare a meta-policy using the X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies HTTP response header.\n\nHowever, our web site and web applications do not use Adobe Flash. As far as we can tell, this header is concerned only with the security of Flash content.","can_view?":true,"can_edit?":false,"content_html":"\u003cp\u003eThe suggestion was to set \u003ccode\u003eX-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: master-only\u003c/code\u003e. From \u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.adobe.com%2Fdevnet-docs%2Facrobatetk%2Ftools%2FAppSec%2Fxdomain.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eAdobe\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e (\u003ca href=\"/redirect?url=https%3A%2F%2Fgithub.com%2Ftwitter%2Fsecureheaders%2Fissues%2F88\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003eper\u003c/span\u003e\u003ci class=\"icon-external-link\"\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/a\u003e):\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNormally a meta-policy is declared in the master policy file, but for those who can’t write to the root directory, they can also declare a meta-policy using the X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies HTTP response header.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, our web site and web applications do not use Adobe Flash. As far as we can tell, this header is concerned only with the security of Flash content.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"category":"researcher","can_view?":true,"can_create?":false}]}